column5: Hi Guys, Has anyone overnighted in S.L. this year? I see that the SUNSET INN has re opened... is it "stayable" Horrible stay last year at the LAMPLIGHTER... Seems the only choice left is FOREST INN... Anyone stay at either places this year ?
there is a solid amount of air BNBs on their website. might be a better option

Not this year, but last August. Stayed in the outbuilding next to the bar on a Friday night. Had a good meal at the restaurant, no issues with bar noise or patrons. It was actually pretty quiet. Room was a little "tired" is all. If we go back that way we would stay there again
Stayed at the Forest Inn in early June. Rooms were fine and restaurant was good.
Stayed at sunset last week. Under construction but room was clean and motel six quality. Be careful in the parking lot as we picked up a nail.
So motel six,they must have left the light on for ya Big root!pick up those nails so they don't enter a tire.
We stayed at Forest Inn in June also. Happy with room and food.
